Actually as part of a security task force I did some checking on
the integrity of the Berkeley REXEC system.  It is very difficult
at all to spoof internet addresses in a way that will fool REXEC
if you not on the same net as the host you are trying to fool.

The way REXEC works is to ringback a specific host/port after
vailidation.  The gateway has its own notion of where to route
things, so the security problem is not present, as long as you
stay within your own autonomous system.

Nameservers do not enter into this as long as you use the numbers.

-Ron

